{"id": "EUVD-2025-28975", "enisaUuid": "6df2928b-e6c6-3ea2-a3bc-3cfe35602ec7", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/kmemleak: avoid deadlock by moving pr_warn() outside kmemleak_lock\n\nWhen netpoll is enabled, calling pr_warn_once() while holding\nkmemleak_lock in mem_pool_alloc() can cause a deadlock due to lock\ninversion with the netconsole subsystem.  This occurs because\npr_warn_once() may trigger netpoll, which eventually leads to\n__alloc_skb() and back into kmemleak code, attempting to reacquire\nkmemleak_lock.\n\nThis is the path for the deadlock.\n\nmem_pool_alloc()\n  -> raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&kmemleak_lock, flags);\n      -> pr_warn_once()\n          -> netconsole subsystem\n\t     -> netpoll\n\t         -> __alloc_skb\n\t\t   -> __create_object\n\t\t     -> raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&kmemleak_lock, flags);\n\nFix this by setting a flag and issuing the pr_warn_once() after\nkmemleak_lock is released.", "datePublished": "2025-09-11T18:35:50", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T18:31:40", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c7b6ea0ede687e7460e593c5ea478f50aa41682a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4b0151e1d468eb2667c37b7af99b3c075072d334", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f249d32bb54876b4b6c3ae071af8ddca77af390b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/62879faa8efe8d8a9c7bf7606ee9c068012d7dac", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1da95d3d4b7b1d380ebd87b71a61e7e6aed3265d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a0854de00ce2ee27edf39037e7836ad580eb3350", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/08f70be5e406ce47c822f2dd11c1170ca259605b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a181b228b37a6a5625dad2bb4265bb7abb673e9f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/47b0f6d8f0d2be4d311a49e13d2fd5f152f492b2", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39736", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00007.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00008.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39736"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "11fa2f08-e354-36ba-998c-05737911f746", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.2"}, {"id": "22c2558c-ec2b-378e-a38e-6187a0c22682", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "29d44fd5-fff4-3f0f-a8ee-e6af1ac031ca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <4b0151e1d468eb2667c37b7af99b3c075072d334"}, {"id": "359c2e8d-f76b-3548-b202-c8478f9b36ef", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <f249d32bb54876b4b6c3ae071af8ddca77af390b"}, {"id": "3e44d0c3-2e09-3ea9-a6ae-48cd0f45b023", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <c7b6ea0ede687e7460e593c5ea478f50aa41682a"}, {"id": "468d0c7e-538b-312f-9cc3-2cac81fc117b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.241"}, {"id": "5d190591-bd38-3e1f-ae4b-206760a98056", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.43"}, {"id": "6a5b7aca-e5af-38a6-ab31-179d6f4bfe0c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.11"}, {"id": "718fd6f0-1531-307c-8fea-592d23b07899", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <62879faa8efe8d8a9c7bf7606ee9c068012d7dac"}, {"id": "816f2017-14af-3ec9-acec-a2a0b68c27ed", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <08f70be5e406ce47c822f2dd11c1170ca259605b"}, {"id": "837212e1-eb0e-3ade-ad34-4106274bb6bb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "83e5b562-a656-3298-a211-fde30f6826d6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.190"}, {"id": "884e96dc-4087-3ec3-b2d8-7d06779578aa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5665868183fec689dbab9fb8505188b2c4f0757 <a181b228b37a6a5625dad2bb4265bb7abb673e9f"}, {"id": "932c4652-d2d0-3aa0-9ab6-c6e87c41e794", "product